docs/logic/DETERMINISTIC_LEGAL_PARSER_IMPROVEMENT_PLAN.md:145:The encoder is the parser path that maps source text into `LegalNormIR`. The decoder is a source-grounded rendering layer that maps `LegalNormIR` back into normalized legal text. The decoder is not a language model and should not add facts that are absent from the IR. Its job is to expose whether the IR preserved the legally salient content needed to reconstruct the clause.
